1
00:00:43,252 --> 00:00:50,217
CHAPTER 46:
EVEN IF I HAVE TO DROP OUT

2
00:01:00,811 --> 00:01:01,896
What time does it start?

3
00:01:03,272 --> 00:01:05,524
Nine o'clock. I think.

4
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:07,276
Amazing.

5
00:01:07,902 --> 00:01:09,945
Being summoned to
the disciplinary committee.

6
00:01:10,654 --> 00:01:11,739
Just eat your breakfast.

7
00:01:14,408 --> 00:01:16,035
Sounds like your novel's a huge hit.

8
00:01:16,535 --> 00:01:17,453
What's the problem?

9
00:01:17,536 --> 00:01:18,829
Earn money from writing.

10
00:01:19,371 --> 00:01:22,041
Make a killing
and give me a huge allowance.

11
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,710
You can just drop out and take the GED.

12
00:01:31,717 --> 00:01:33,135
We might be your parents,

13
00:01:33,219 --> 00:01:35,721
but we won't necessarily take your side.

14
00:01:35,805 --> 00:01:38,974
We're going to accept whatever punishment
the school decides to give you.

15
00:01:39,058 --> 00:01:39,934
Okay?

16
00:01:40,935 --> 00:01:42,019
Honey…

17
00:02:00,287 --> 00:02:01,914
What's our game plan today?

18
00:02:04,625 --> 00:02:06,502
Shouldn't we present a united front?

19
00:02:09,380 --> 00:02:11,298
I'll go with the flow.

20
00:02:11,382 --> 00:02:12,299
Me too.

21
00:02:14,969 --> 00:02:16,971
I believe if Eui-ju hopes to keep writing

22
00:02:18,055 --> 00:02:19,473
and pursue it as a career,

23
00:02:21,016 --> 00:02:23,143
she needs to learn something from this.

24
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:33,320
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

25
00:02:36,782 --> 00:02:38,826
EPISODE 15

26
00:02:57,011 --> 00:02:58,387
DISCIPLINARY COMMITTEE

27
00:03:11,734 --> 00:03:14,278
GRADE HEAD, MS. JANG
HEAD OF STUDENT AFFAIRS, MR. SONG

28
00:03:14,361 --> 00:03:15,446
We are gathered today…

29
00:03:15,529 --> 00:03:16,614
VICE PRINCIPAL, MR. SEO

30
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:17,823
…to discuss the novel

31
00:03:17,907 --> 00:03:23,329
written by Yeo Eui-ju
featuring her teachers as characters.

32
00:03:23,412 --> 00:03:26,457
I'm sure you all gathered
that the characters in the novel

33
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:28,834
are based on the teachers of this school.

34
00:03:28,918 --> 00:03:32,671
This is a severe violation
of teachers' rights and defamation.

35
00:03:33,297 --> 00:03:36,216
Please share your opinions
on what we should do.

36
00:03:37,051 --> 00:03:37,968
Ms. Kim,

37
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:41,639
I was so shaken
that I couldn't bring myself to finish it.

38
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:44,725
My gosh, what a total shock.

39
00:03:46,352 --> 00:03:48,687
I know curiosity can prompt students
to make a mistake.

40
00:03:49,605 --> 00:03:50,689
However,

41
00:03:50,773 --> 00:03:53,984
this is when their sexual identity
and values should be forming.

42
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:56,445
If one goes down the wrong path like this,

43
00:03:56,528 --> 00:03:58,864
we, as adults, have to correct them
sooner or later.

44
00:03:59,865 --> 00:04:01,951
Since she is still a minor,

45
00:04:02,034 --> 00:04:03,869
let's prevent her from becoming a criminal

46
00:04:04,453 --> 00:04:05,704
by giving her a heavy penalty.

47
00:04:06,288 --> 00:04:07,164
Crim…

48
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:09,458
Criminal?

49
00:04:10,459 --> 00:04:11,835
Ms. Oh, what did you think

50
00:04:11,919 --> 00:04:14,004
about the novel your daughter wrote?

51
00:04:15,214 --> 00:04:16,173
Well…

52
00:04:16,757 --> 00:04:17,591
Then,

53
00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:21,011
let me just say a few words.

54
00:04:21,762 --> 00:04:25,224
Firstly, my daughter has caused
everyone gathered here

55
00:04:25,307 --> 00:04:28,519
discomfort and concern.

56
00:04:29,228 --> 00:04:31,522
For that,
I'd like to offer my sincere apology.

57
00:04:32,564 --> 00:04:35,526
It is all my fault
due to my shortcomings as a parent.

58
00:04:36,443 --> 00:04:39,905
I should have paid more attention.

59
00:04:43,075 --> 00:04:43,909
However!

60
00:04:47,871 --> 00:04:48,872
How can we as parents

61
00:04:49,915 --> 00:04:52,459
stop something like this?

62
00:04:55,254 --> 00:04:56,088
My child

63
00:04:56,714 --> 00:04:58,674
says it's her lifeline.

64
00:05:00,092 --> 00:05:01,385
She's still young,

65
00:05:02,052 --> 00:05:04,680
so she lacks good judgment.

66
00:05:05,889 --> 00:05:08,684
If you would just give her the chance
to reflect on her mistakes,

67
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:10,019
I'd be truly grateful.

68
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:13,814
-Please.
-Please.

69
00:05:18,944 --> 00:05:22,406
As the victims here, what do you think?

70
00:05:23,699 --> 00:05:24,825
Well…

71
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:25,951
First off,

72
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:30,289
I will speak on behalf of all four of us.

73
00:05:32,291 --> 00:05:35,085
The fact that Eui-ju
was pairing us up in her stories

74
00:05:35,169 --> 00:05:36,628
left us shocked and stunned.

75
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:41,383
We wondered, "Is this what she fantasizes
when she looks at us?"

76
00:05:41,467 --> 00:05:42,301
Such thoughts

77
00:05:42,968 --> 00:05:44,511
gave us much discomfort too.

78
00:05:47,806 --> 00:05:49,058
Regarding this whole affair,

79
00:05:49,141 --> 00:05:50,642
we've given it a lot of thought.

80
00:05:51,310 --> 00:05:53,937
After much consideration,
we've come to the conclusion.

81
00:06:01,779 --> 00:06:03,572
What do you think we should do, ma'am?

82
00:06:07,159 --> 00:06:10,162
We will accept whatever you decide.

83
00:06:11,663 --> 00:06:12,748
Oh.

84
00:06:16,043 --> 00:06:17,211
What about the rest of you?

85
00:06:18,337 --> 00:06:20,547
Even with adaptations to reality,

86
00:06:20,631 --> 00:06:23,300
writing real people into a novel
without their consent

87
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:24,718
is a serious matter

88
00:06:25,636 --> 00:06:27,304
and shouldn't be taken lightly.

89
00:06:28,138 --> 00:06:29,765
I hope Eui-ju will learn this lesson.

90
00:06:34,269 --> 00:06:36,063
We all know the saying,
"Turn the other cheek."

91
00:06:39,483 --> 00:06:40,317
I've…

92
00:06:41,485 --> 00:06:42,986
decided to do just that.

93
00:06:45,072 --> 00:06:46,323
What kind of nonsense is that?

94
00:06:47,074 --> 00:06:48,784
If we let this go
with a slap on her wrist,

95
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:50,994
the school's authority will collapse.

96
00:06:51,078 --> 00:06:52,454
She must be expelled!

97
00:06:53,163 --> 00:06:54,998
I recommend expulsion.

98
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:04,091
I'm the one who's responsible.

99
00:07:09,805 --> 00:07:11,765
I knew all about Eui-ju's novel,

100
00:07:12,391 --> 00:07:14,143
and I told her to keep writing.

101
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:24,820
Of course, at first,
I told her to delete it.

102
00:07:24,903 --> 00:07:26,363
I couldn't understand her.

103
00:07:26,905 --> 00:07:28,115
However, Eui-ju

104
00:07:28,991 --> 00:07:30,784
had a clear vision for her future

105
00:07:30,868 --> 00:07:32,369
and was working toward her dream.

106
00:07:32,995 --> 00:07:34,538
Her confidence was so firm,

107
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:37,749
I found myself almost envious of it.

108
00:07:43,172 --> 00:07:44,673
So, I encouraged her to keep writing.

109
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:47,426
I wanted to trust her, watch over her,

110
00:07:48,677 --> 00:07:49,845
and cheer her on.

111
00:07:54,558 --> 00:07:55,809
Eui-ju

112
00:07:57,060 --> 00:08:00,230
is the type of student who sees it through
once she sets her mind to something.

113
00:08:01,565 --> 00:08:02,900
As her homeroom teacher,

114
00:08:02,983 --> 00:08:04,985
I've observed her
and come to appreciate her tenacity.

115
00:08:06,528 --> 00:08:08,989
Since it is Eui-ju's dream
to become a writer,

116
00:08:09,072 --> 00:08:12,034
please let her tenacity
blossom into a true strength,

117
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:16,413
and allow her energy and passion
to help her achieve her dreams

118
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:19,458
by giving her another chance.

119
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:22,920
Please, just think about it.

120
00:08:34,473 --> 00:08:35,474
Let's hear

121
00:08:36,099 --> 00:08:37,517
what you intend to do.

122
00:08:38,310 --> 00:08:39,728
Are you going to keep writing?

123
00:08:39,811 --> 00:08:40,854
You won't, right?

124
00:08:44,107 --> 00:08:44,983
I…

125
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:46,401
Yes?

126
00:08:53,075 --> 00:08:54,034
I…

127
00:09:00,082 --> 00:09:02,251
I want to keep writing.

128
00:09:03,168 --> 00:09:04,294
What?

129
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:08,090
I will take whatever punishment
I am given,

130
00:09:09,258 --> 00:09:10,175
and keep on writing

131
00:09:10,926 --> 00:09:13,470
after crafting a story of my own
and deliberating on its elements.

132
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:18,767
I've been reflecting on my actions,
and I'm sincerely sorry.

133
00:09:19,434 --> 00:09:21,478
I've deleted We Were Friends.

134
00:09:23,605 --> 00:09:25,190
However, when it comes to writing…

135
00:09:28,402 --> 00:09:29,778
I want to keep pursuing it.

136
00:09:32,322 --> 00:09:33,949
Even if I have to drop out,

137
00:09:36,201 --> 00:09:38,078
I will keep writing novels.

138
00:09:53,135 --> 00:09:55,470
I will discuss this
with the other teachers.

139
00:09:55,554 --> 00:09:56,722
And as for punishment,

140
00:09:57,973 --> 00:10:01,143
I will let you know in four days.
Let's go.

141
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:09,943
-Goodbye.
-Thank you.

142
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:17,451
I'm truly sorry.

143
00:10:18,035 --> 00:10:19,745
I'm sorry.

144
00:10:19,828 --> 00:10:22,873
Mr. Ga, back then,

145
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:25,584
I didn't realize
you were Eui-ju's homeroom teacher.

146
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:26,710
Don't worry about it.

147
00:10:27,502 --> 00:10:29,212
I should have looked out for her.

148
00:10:30,589 --> 00:10:32,507
Don't worry too much. Get home safely.

149
00:10:32,591 --> 00:10:33,425
Okay.

150
00:10:34,676 --> 00:10:36,470
I'll go and talk to Ms. Kim.

151
00:10:36,553 --> 00:10:37,554
-Okay.
-Sure.

152
00:10:49,107 --> 00:10:51,985
Mom, Dad. You can go now.

153
00:10:52,569 --> 00:10:53,653
Go?

154
00:10:54,780 --> 00:10:55,781
Oh, right.

155
00:10:55,864 --> 00:10:57,908
Then, we'll be off.

156
00:10:57,991 --> 00:10:59,368
-I'll see you at home.
-Sure.

157
00:10:59,451 --> 00:11:00,452
All right, then.

158
00:11:00,535 --> 00:11:01,745
-Goodbye.
-Have a safe trip home.

159
00:11:02,704 --> 00:11:03,705
Pay attention in class.

160
00:11:07,292 --> 00:11:08,460
You can get back to class.

161
00:11:08,543 --> 00:11:10,796
We have to wait for Mr. Ga.

162
00:11:16,718 --> 00:11:18,637
I'm sorry for what I did.

163
00:11:23,225 --> 00:11:25,227
I never expected to end up
in one of your early projects.

164
00:11:25,977 --> 00:11:28,146
I'm really sorry, Mr. Yoon.

165
00:11:29,564 --> 00:11:33,151
Writers observe, imagine, and write,

166
00:11:33,235 --> 00:11:36,488
but when dealing with real people,
we have to be careful.

167
00:11:37,072 --> 00:11:38,073
Do you get that now?

168
00:11:39,366 --> 00:11:40,200
Yes, sir.

169
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,035
So troublesome.

170
00:11:42,119 --> 00:11:44,704
That letter she wrote in my class
was a big fat indicator.

171
00:11:44,788 --> 00:11:48,250
It was so rambling.

172
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:52,379
I'm going to be keeping a close eye
on your Japanese essay assignment.

173
00:11:53,255 --> 00:11:55,590
If it doesn't move me emotionally,

174
00:11:55,674 --> 00:11:57,092
I'll give you an F for sure.

175
00:11:57,717 --> 00:11:58,552
Yes, sir.

176
00:11:58,635 --> 00:12:00,262
You're in big trouble now.

177
00:12:00,846 --> 00:12:02,556
Sir, I'm really sorry. I put you through--

178
00:12:02,639 --> 00:12:03,890
No need to apologize.

179
00:12:03,974 --> 00:12:05,392
I don't know much about writing anyway.

180
00:12:07,102 --> 00:12:08,061
But from what I hear,

181
00:12:08,687 --> 00:12:09,729
you have a knack for it.

182
00:12:10,856 --> 00:12:11,857
You do, don't you?

183
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:12,941
That's all that matters.

184
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:16,945
Don't worry too much.
Now, go back to class.

185
00:12:18,697 --> 00:12:19,531
Yes, sir.

186
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:27,497
Just a moment.

187
00:12:28,748 --> 00:12:32,085
The more I think about it,
the more libelous it seems.

188
00:12:33,211 --> 00:12:34,963
I can't just forget it and move on.

189
00:12:35,046 --> 00:12:36,548
I simply have to

190
00:12:36,631 --> 00:12:39,050
retain a lawyer
and see this through to the end.

191
00:12:39,134 --> 00:12:41,052
He's joking.

192
00:12:41,136 --> 00:12:42,095
You're good to go.

193
00:12:42,179 --> 00:12:45,098
Why did you portray me as being so petty?

194
00:12:45,682 --> 00:12:46,641
Seriously though,

195
00:12:47,225 --> 00:12:50,353
do I look like someone who'd hide
rather than stand up to injustice?

196
00:12:50,437 --> 00:12:52,731
-You don't stand up to injustice.
-I do!

197
00:12:52,814 --> 00:12:54,024
I do, don't I?

198
00:12:55,692 --> 00:12:58,278
Hey, kid. What if people think
that's what I'm really like?

199
00:12:58,361 --> 00:13:00,280
-That is what you're like.
-No, I'm not.

200
00:13:00,363 --> 00:13:01,865
-You did a good job.
-Great writing.

201
00:13:01,948 --> 00:13:04,034
Yeah, his character was the best.

202
00:13:05,202 --> 00:13:06,620
Don't listen to him. Just go.

203
00:13:06,703 --> 00:13:07,746
-Off you go.
-Good work.

204
00:13:07,829 --> 00:13:09,956
Hey, you need to make some changes.

205
00:13:10,040 --> 00:13:11,666
Come on, revise my character!

206
00:13:16,254 --> 00:13:17,255
-What happened?
-Eui-ju.

207
00:13:17,339 --> 00:13:18,507
-Hey, Eui-ju.
-Eui-ju.

208
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:20,759
-What happened?
-What did they say?

209
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:22,219
-What's the verdict?
-What happened?

210
00:13:22,302 --> 00:13:24,596
-What's the result?
-I don't know yet.

211
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:26,056
They'll discuss and let me know.

212
00:13:26,139 --> 00:13:27,140
-Oh, no.
-Then,

213
00:13:27,224 --> 00:13:29,726
are they going to let you know today?

214
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:30,769
What did they say?

215
00:13:30,852 --> 00:13:32,479
Come on, say something.

216
00:13:32,562 --> 00:13:34,105
What did Mr. Ga say?

217
00:13:34,189 --> 00:13:35,398
Didn't he say anything?

218
00:13:35,482 --> 00:13:36,858
-Huh?
-To tell the truth,

219
00:13:37,859 --> 00:13:40,737
he already knew about it.

220
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,697
-He caught me.
-What?

221
00:13:42,781 --> 00:13:45,367
-He knew about it?
-How?

222
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:49,287
Since he knew and let me keep writing,

223
00:13:49,371 --> 00:13:51,498
he said it was his fault.

224
00:13:51,581 --> 00:13:52,832
Mr. Ga did?

225
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:54,751
-I see.
-Really?

226
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:55,919
He knew about it?

227
00:13:56,002 --> 00:13:58,838
-So he knew all along.
-He knew.

228
00:13:58,922 --> 00:14:01,049
-So what's going to happen?
-If he knew…

229
00:14:01,132 --> 00:14:03,009
They're having a meeting now.

230
00:14:04,719 --> 00:14:07,639
Her work was just as popular
as the works of established writers.

231
00:14:08,515 --> 00:14:09,516
If it were a real book,

232
00:14:09,599 --> 00:14:12,435
it would have been an instant bestseller.

233
00:14:13,436 --> 00:14:15,564
So what if it's popular?

234
00:14:15,647 --> 00:14:17,399
It's still unseemly.

235
00:14:18,483 --> 00:14:19,859
In the early days of online novels,

236
00:14:19,943 --> 00:14:22,153
there was a writer
with the pen name Love Hani.

237
00:14:22,779 --> 00:14:25,156
Initially, her work
received brutal criticisms,

238
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:27,117
but it was so popular
that it was made into a movie.

239
00:14:28,326 --> 00:14:31,830
Love Hani even donated
some of her royalties to her alma mater.

240
00:14:32,789 --> 00:14:34,708
Think how proud the school must have been.

241
00:14:34,791 --> 00:14:36,251
She donated her royalties?

242
00:14:39,504 --> 00:14:40,880
Even so, this is unacceptable.

243
00:14:41,590 --> 00:14:42,841
I simply can't abide it.

244
00:14:44,634 --> 00:14:46,845
Mr. Song,
what are you reading so intently?

245
00:14:47,512 --> 00:14:49,472
Ms. Kim, the thing is,

246
00:14:49,556 --> 00:14:50,807
this is a big deal indeed.

247
00:14:51,308 --> 00:14:52,142
I said so, didn't I?

248
00:14:52,225 --> 00:14:53,810
It seems Eui-ju's novel

249
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:56,187
is quite something.

250
00:14:56,688 --> 00:14:59,274
People are losing it
in the comments of her notice,

251
00:14:59,357 --> 00:15:00,775
asking why she took her work down.

252
00:15:00,859 --> 00:15:02,319
Don't be silly.

253
00:15:03,486 --> 00:15:04,654
How many people read it?

254
00:15:04,738 --> 00:15:06,865
A thousand tops?

255
00:15:07,449 --> 00:15:10,035
Way more than a thousand.

256
00:15:10,118 --> 00:15:12,162
Just counting comments alone,

257
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:14,247
there are 108,420 so far.

258
00:15:14,331 --> 00:15:17,083
What? That many people have seen it?

259
00:15:19,544 --> 00:15:21,504
Even so, this is unacceptable.

260
00:15:21,588 --> 00:15:23,590
A student using their teachers like that.

261
00:15:23,673 --> 00:15:25,717
Oh, wow.

262
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:28,470
They've even got a petition going.

263
00:15:28,553 --> 00:15:30,597
"The Committee for the Return of Imuk."

264
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:31,806
Mr. Song.

265
00:15:34,476 --> 00:15:36,353
To be honest, my biggest concern now

266
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:39,481
is the damage to the school's reputation
if the word gets out.

267
00:15:39,981 --> 00:15:42,233
No, we can look at it another way.

268
00:15:42,317 --> 00:15:46,488
"Our school cultivated a student
with this degree of literary talent."

269
00:15:47,072 --> 00:15:48,114
Mr. Song.

270
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:53,578
That is something to be grateful for.

271
00:15:55,747 --> 00:15:58,083
She could become a famous writer
like what's-her-name

272
00:15:58,166 --> 00:16:00,126
who wrote the Harry Potter series.

273
00:16:00,210 --> 00:16:01,920
Anything's possible, right?

274
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:03,588
Sure.

275
00:16:03,672 --> 00:16:04,756
You're so right, ma'am.

276
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:06,758
Let me think.

277
00:16:09,344 --> 00:16:10,679
What should we do?

278
00:16:15,767 --> 00:16:19,104
4 DAYS LATER

279
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:24,484
Your actions in this instance

280
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:27,278
were not only a serious violation
of school regulations,

281
00:16:27,362 --> 00:16:31,491
but also had a negative impact
on other students.

282
00:16:36,329 --> 00:16:38,665
However, since you have shown contrition,

283
00:16:38,748 --> 00:16:41,376
we acknowledge your willingness to reform.

284
00:16:41,459 --> 00:16:44,212
As such, we'll give you one last chance.

285
00:16:44,921 --> 00:16:46,423
You will be punished,

286
00:16:46,923 --> 00:16:49,509
but we will not stop you
from pursuing your dream.

287
00:16:51,136 --> 00:16:55,473
Accordingly, the school's decision
on this matter is…

288
00:17:05,817 --> 00:17:07,444
that you will be suspended for five days.

289
00:17:18,997 --> 00:17:19,873
One more thing,

290
00:17:20,999 --> 00:17:21,958
am I in it too?

291
00:17:24,169 --> 00:17:26,212
-What happened?
-What did you get?

292
00:17:26,838 --> 00:17:27,881
Suspended…

293
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:30,091
for five days.

294
00:17:30,925 --> 00:17:31,885
-Suspended?
-Suspended?

295
00:17:31,968 --> 00:17:34,596
-Suspended!
-Wow, suspended!

296
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:42,270
Wait, is being suspended
better than being expelled?

297
00:17:42,937 --> 00:17:44,647
But what about college?

298
00:17:44,731 --> 00:17:48,067
Even places that consider practicals only
will still check your record.

299
00:17:48,943 --> 00:17:50,904
No.

300
00:17:50,987 --> 00:17:53,782
As long as it's not for school violence,
it won't appear on her record.

301
00:17:53,865 --> 00:17:55,366
-Really?
-As far as I know.

302
00:17:55,450 --> 00:17:58,119
Whatever happens, it was my fault,
so I have to accept it.

303
00:17:59,496 --> 00:18:01,414
Don't be so serious.

304
00:18:01,498 --> 00:18:03,082
It's just a suspension!

305
00:18:07,921 --> 00:18:09,672
-Oh, it's Mr. Ga.
-It's Mr. Ga.

306
00:18:12,258 --> 00:18:15,136
CHAPTER 47:
BECAUSE YOU'RE MY FIRST STUDENT

307
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:17,180
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

308
00:18:26,815 --> 00:18:28,441
As you've probably already heard,

309
00:18:29,067 --> 00:18:30,568
Eui-ju has been suspended.

310
00:18:35,448 --> 00:18:38,117
It's only correct that she takes
responsibility for her actions.

311
00:18:38,201 --> 00:18:39,494
However,

312
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:41,079
it's also partly my fault.

313
00:18:42,580 --> 00:18:44,916
As a teacher,
I shouldn't favor any one student,

314
00:18:45,542 --> 00:18:46,709
and in that, I failed.

315
00:18:49,546 --> 00:18:51,339
If anyone was hurt by what has happened,

316
00:18:52,298 --> 00:18:53,508
I apologize.

317
00:18:56,010 --> 00:18:58,596
From now on,
I'll listen to all of you more.

318
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:01,349
So instead of taking sides
about who was right or wrong,

319
00:19:01,432 --> 00:19:04,018
I hope you'll try
to understand each other.

320
00:19:04,602 --> 00:19:05,812
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

321
00:19:06,938 --> 00:19:08,648
Okay, enjoy class. I'll see you later.

322
00:19:09,566 --> 00:19:11,025
I'm sorry.

323
00:19:12,026 --> 00:19:12,944
Sorry.

324
00:19:16,364 --> 00:19:17,282
Thanks.

325
00:19:36,593 --> 00:19:37,427
What now?

326
00:19:38,469 --> 00:19:41,514
I didn't get the chance
to properly thank you.

327
00:19:42,265 --> 00:19:43,516
Thank you, Mr. Ga.

328
00:19:45,101 --> 00:19:46,311
There's no need.

329
00:19:47,687 --> 00:19:48,730
By the way,

330
00:19:49,564 --> 00:19:50,940
Mr. Ga,

331
00:19:51,024 --> 00:19:52,609
why did you do it?

332
00:19:53,902 --> 00:19:54,736
What?

333
00:19:55,695 --> 00:19:59,532
You convinced
the principal and the other teachers

334
00:19:59,616 --> 00:20:01,284
to be on my side

335
00:20:01,367 --> 00:20:02,660
when I'm just a silly nobody.

336
00:20:18,676 --> 00:20:19,719
To me, you're…

337
00:20:29,145 --> 00:20:30,229
Because you're…

338
00:20:38,446 --> 00:20:39,656
my first student.

339
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:48,665
Just because

340
00:20:50,083 --> 00:20:51,459
I'm your student?

341
00:20:55,088 --> 00:20:56,798
Whether Ji-a, Ha-su, or you,

342
00:20:57,465 --> 00:21:00,009
you're all kids
I have to turn the other cheek to.

343
00:21:03,471 --> 00:21:05,807
Don't get into trouble
while you're suspended.

344
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:07,141
Now, go home.

345
00:21:29,914 --> 00:21:34,836
CHAPTER 48:
TURN OVER A NEW LEAF

346
00:21:35,795 --> 00:21:37,797
What? You can't eat this.

347
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:40,341
Suni, go and wake Eui-ju.

348
00:21:40,883 --> 00:21:42,552
All right.

349
00:21:48,683 --> 00:21:49,726
Bang.

350
00:22:05,158 --> 00:22:06,159
YEO EUI-JU

351
00:22:15,710 --> 00:22:16,711
I'm giving it a shot too.

352
00:22:21,924 --> 00:22:23,885
I've always run away
without seeing things through,

353
00:22:25,094 --> 00:22:26,429
but I'm done with that.

354
00:22:29,974 --> 00:22:31,267
What do you mean?

355
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:32,685
Who are you talking about?

356
00:22:37,982 --> 00:22:38,941
Are you going somewhere?

357
00:22:39,692 --> 00:22:40,526
What's this about?

358
00:22:43,154 --> 00:22:45,073
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

359
00:22:46,324 --> 00:22:47,533
What's this?

360
00:22:48,326 --> 00:22:51,079
I know we're supposed to get you tofu,
but this should do the trick.

361
00:22:51,662 --> 00:22:54,248
-Isn't this actually…
-It's for the better.

362
00:22:54,332 --> 00:22:55,541
Don't fuss like she served time.

363
00:22:55,625 --> 00:22:57,126
-What?
-It's pretty much the same.

364
00:22:57,210 --> 00:22:59,545
-Yeah.
-Think of her as being released.

365
00:22:59,629 --> 00:23:01,172
It's time to turn over a new leaf, buddy.

366
00:23:01,255 --> 00:23:02,256
Of course.

367
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:03,633
Thanks, buddy.

368
00:23:05,218 --> 00:23:06,552
-Isn't it so nice?
-Here.

369
00:23:06,636 --> 00:23:07,887
Eat these when you write.

370
00:23:07,970 --> 00:23:09,972
Can't have you go hungry, right?

371
00:23:10,056 --> 00:23:11,432
-Wow, that's expensive.
-Thanks.

372
00:23:11,516 --> 00:23:13,101
-How sweet!
-It's nothing.

373
00:23:13,184 --> 00:23:14,560
I can't believe my friend

374
00:23:15,603 --> 00:23:17,772
is a mega-hit writer!

375
00:23:17,855 --> 00:23:19,857
Eui-ju, you got this.

376
00:23:19,941 --> 00:23:21,192
-You got this!
-You got this!

377
00:23:21,275 --> 00:23:23,194
-You got this!
-You're amazing!

378
00:23:23,277 --> 00:23:24,570
-Go on!
-Try it!

379
00:23:24,654 --> 00:23:26,197
You have to eat something white

380
00:23:26,280 --> 00:23:27,824
-to mark your fresh start.
-I'll be good.

381
00:23:27,907 --> 00:23:28,950
To a fresh start!

382
00:23:47,468 --> 00:23:48,302
I…

383
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:52,765
didn't like that Mr. Ga
was giving you so much attention.

384
00:23:56,185 --> 00:23:58,479
I thought if I ruined you,

385
00:23:58,563 --> 00:24:00,940
he would notice me.

386
00:24:03,484 --> 00:24:04,819
But that's not what happened.

387
00:24:07,822 --> 00:24:09,282
I'm not trying to make excuses.

388
00:24:10,825 --> 00:24:12,535
I just wanted to tell you

389
00:24:13,828 --> 00:24:15,121
that I'm sorry.

390
00:24:24,297 --> 00:24:28,759
It's thanks to you that
I was able to acknowledge my mistakes.

391
00:24:28,843 --> 00:24:30,428
If none of this had happened,

392
00:24:30,511 --> 00:24:32,930
I would've kept writing
with a sense of guilt.

393
00:24:42,231 --> 00:24:43,399
Let's get to the auditorium.

394
00:24:44,066 --> 00:24:46,402
The auditorium? Not homeroom?

395
00:24:46,485 --> 00:24:49,113
There's a special lecture
by Professor Na Deul-i.

396
00:24:49,197 --> 00:24:52,241
Do you think she's Mr. Ga's girlfriend?

397
00:24:52,325 --> 00:24:54,827
One, two, this is a mic test. Check.

398
00:24:54,911 --> 00:24:55,870
Say ho, ho, ho!

399
00:24:55,953 --> 00:24:56,871
-Ho, ho, ho!
-Ho, ho, ho!

400
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:02,793
Dan-ji wants me to bring
the projector remote from the AV room.

401
00:25:02,877 --> 00:25:03,878
You go ahead.

402
00:25:03,961 --> 00:25:04,879
Okay.

403
00:25:20,311 --> 00:25:21,479
Hello.

404
00:25:22,104 --> 00:25:23,147
Oh, hello.

405
00:25:24,398 --> 00:25:26,734
You're the student I met
at the coffee shop that time, right?

406
00:25:28,819 --> 00:25:30,279
It's nice to see a familiar face.

407
00:25:31,405 --> 00:25:33,699
I'm shaking with nerves.

408
00:25:34,575 --> 00:25:35,576
Why?

409
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:40,289
I've never really interacted
with teenagers.

410
00:25:41,249 --> 00:25:42,792
I hear teenagers these days can be scary.

411
00:25:43,542 --> 00:25:45,127
I'm worried I might say the wrong thing.

412
00:25:47,088 --> 00:25:48,422
We're not that bad.

413
00:25:49,006 --> 00:25:50,925
We don't bite unless you try
and steal our food.

414
00:25:59,141 --> 00:26:00,643
Are you here for this?

415
00:26:00,726 --> 00:26:02,353
-Yes, sir.
-Let's go.

416
00:26:03,437 --> 00:26:04,647
Do you think I'll be okay?

417
00:26:05,648 --> 00:26:08,025
Why not? You've lectured
to a bigger audience before.

418
00:26:08,109 --> 00:26:10,736
I still feel nervous, all right?

419
00:26:12,863 --> 00:26:14,073
Wish me luck!

420
00:26:16,784 --> 00:26:18,286
You'll be fine.

421
00:26:18,369 --> 00:26:20,746
I'm telling you it's my first time
somewhere like this.

422
00:26:27,628 --> 00:26:28,504
Eui-ju.

423
00:26:29,505 --> 00:26:30,506
What did she want?

424
00:26:30,589 --> 00:26:31,841
We made up.

425
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:33,884
Made up?

426
00:26:33,968 --> 00:26:34,969
Yeah, made up.

427
00:26:37,972 --> 00:26:41,142
IN MY OWN WAY,
AT A PACE THAT SUITS ME

428
00:26:43,227 --> 00:26:45,855
Hello, everyone.
It's great to be here. I'm Na Deul-i.

429
00:26:46,772 --> 00:26:49,317
I've put together some photos
to show you who I am.

430
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,776
What do you think this is?

431
00:26:50,860 --> 00:26:53,362
It's the first test I ever took
back in first grade.

432
00:26:54,322 --> 00:26:56,532
Weird, right? I'm supposed to be a genius.

433
00:26:57,283 --> 00:26:59,452
What do you consider
when choosing a career?

434
00:26:59,535 --> 00:27:01,454
-Prestige.
-Prestige? Money? Yes, money.

435
00:27:01,537 --> 00:27:05,708
In STEM, is the MBTI T-type
really more common?

436
00:27:05,791 --> 00:27:07,960
"Are you a T-type?
Are you a freaking T-type?"

437
00:27:08,044 --> 00:27:09,712
Studies have discovered a high likelihood.

438
00:27:09,795 --> 00:27:12,006
You should try it for yourselves.

439
00:27:12,089 --> 00:27:16,761
At the time, I was certain
Team Korea would finish first.

440
00:27:16,844 --> 00:27:20,056
But right at the last moment,
someone ended up dropping out,

441
00:27:20,139 --> 00:27:22,099
so we only finished second.

442
00:27:22,183 --> 00:27:23,351
Who do you think that was?

443
00:27:26,062 --> 00:27:29,857
Yes, sitting at the back,
your math teacher, Mr. Ga.

444
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:38,783
I believe someday
you'll each find your own answer.

445
00:27:39,575 --> 00:27:40,576
It's so annoying.

446
00:27:41,494 --> 00:27:42,661
Why is she so damn cool?

447
00:27:44,246 --> 00:27:45,206
I'll be cheering you on.

448
00:27:45,831 --> 00:27:48,459
This is Na Deul-i signing off.

449
00:27:48,959 --> 00:27:49,960
Thank you.

450
00:27:58,469 --> 00:27:59,804
One, two, three.

451
00:28:01,889 --> 00:28:03,140
I'll share it later. Go back in.

452
00:28:03,224 --> 00:28:04,975
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

453
00:28:05,059 --> 00:28:06,685
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

454
00:28:06,769 --> 00:28:08,020
-Please take a photo of me.
-Sir.

455
00:28:08,104 --> 00:28:10,064
-Me too.
-One for me too, sir!

456
00:28:12,608 --> 00:28:14,276
Ready. One, two, three.

457
00:28:15,736 --> 00:28:17,696
-Thank you.
-Can I get one too?

458
00:28:17,780 --> 00:28:19,281
-Nice!
-Thank you.

459
00:28:19,365 --> 00:28:21,242
-One at a time?
-Yes, sir.

460
00:28:21,325 --> 00:28:22,326
Oh, thank you.

461
00:28:24,245 --> 00:28:25,579
One, two, three.

462
00:28:26,956 --> 00:28:28,207
-Thank you.
-One, two, three.

463
00:28:29,291 --> 00:28:30,626
-You're so cool.
-Thank you.

464
00:28:30,709 --> 00:28:32,670
Thank you, Professor. Thank you, sir.

465
00:28:37,466 --> 00:28:38,426
Come over here.

466
00:28:40,261 --> 00:28:41,679
Okay. One, two, three.

467
00:28:44,432 --> 00:28:45,391
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

468
00:28:45,975 --> 00:28:48,769
Thanks to you,
I could relax and do a good job.

469
00:28:48,853 --> 00:28:49,854
Thank you so much.

470
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:53,649
She helped me deal with my nerves.

471
00:28:56,861 --> 00:28:59,530
There's a pop quiz for after-school math.
Go write it on the board.

472
00:29:00,114 --> 00:29:01,949
-Yes, sir.
-Off you go.

473
00:29:02,616 --> 00:29:03,951
-Goodbye.
-Bye.

474
00:29:05,119 --> 00:29:06,245
Let's go.

475
00:29:07,788 --> 00:29:08,873
-Did you take it?
-Yes.

476
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:16,130
Wow, they do look good together.

477
00:29:19,967 --> 00:29:21,010
Sorry.

478
00:29:25,306 --> 00:29:26,557
You don't need to tell me.

479
00:29:27,266 --> 00:29:29,268
They look picture-perfect.

480
00:29:33,522 --> 00:29:34,356
Let's go.

481
00:29:36,901 --> 00:29:39,069
You happy to research alone
instead of joining me in the US?

482
00:29:39,153 --> 00:29:43,532
CHAPTER 49:
THE ABSOLUT VALUE OF ROMANCE

483
00:29:43,616 --> 00:29:44,992
So, from now on, we'll be competing.

484
00:29:46,827 --> 00:29:48,037
To see who gets there first.

485
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:51,123
Or rather, who gets there at all.

486
00:29:52,833 --> 00:29:55,461
Yeah, time will tell

487
00:29:56,212 --> 00:29:58,422
the value of useless pure mathematics.

488
00:30:00,424 --> 00:30:02,009
Don't come crying to me later.

489
00:30:05,012 --> 00:30:06,305
Just get in already.

490
00:30:07,056 --> 00:30:08,807
Okay, I'm going.

491
00:30:10,476 --> 00:30:12,061
-See you.
-Bye!

492
00:30:13,395 --> 00:30:15,856
VISITOR PARKING LOT

493
00:30:28,869 --> 00:30:30,955
-Good afternoon.
-Good afternoon.

494
00:30:31,038 --> 00:30:32,414
We're having a pop quiz today.

495
00:30:32,498 --> 00:30:33,958
You've got 20 minutes.

496
00:30:34,041 --> 00:30:34,959
Pass them back.

497
00:30:53,269 --> 00:30:54,728
PAST MATH EXAM QUESTIONS

498
00:31:01,193 --> 00:31:02,486
3. PROPERTIES OF LOGARITHMIC FUNCTIONS

499
00:31:02,570 --> 00:31:04,738
1. DIFFERENTIATION OF POLYNOMIAL FUNCTIONS
2. MEAN VALUE THEOREM

500
00:31:30,889 --> 00:31:32,224
If you're done, hand it in and go.

501
00:32:06,175 --> 00:32:07,217
Time's up. Bring it here.

502
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:12,681
I said bring it here.

503
00:32:36,538 --> 00:32:37,623
Put it here and go.

504
00:33:20,207 --> 00:33:22,501
Something that stands on its own

505
00:33:22,584 --> 00:33:24,753
independent of comparison.

506
00:33:24,837 --> 00:33:29,508
Something without conditions,
restrictions, or rivals

507
00:33:29,591 --> 00:33:31,176
is called an absolut value.

508
00:33:31,969 --> 00:33:34,388
Find the absolut value
of the following romance.

509
00:33:38,976 --> 00:33:41,478
What is the absolut value of
glasses divided by pigeon

510
00:33:41,562 --> 00:33:43,188
multiplied by the square root
of emergency room

511
00:33:43,272 --> 00:33:46,608
plus the square
of after-school classes plus novel

512
00:33:46,692 --> 00:33:49,236
multiplied by the limit of bus stop?

513
00:34:18,891 --> 00:34:22,269
ABSOLUTE
ABSOLUTE

514
00:34:23,061 --> 00:34:24,813
-Unbelievable.
-Don't you know how to spell?

515
00:34:26,899 --> 00:34:28,192
Of course, I do.

516
00:34:29,318 --> 00:34:30,486
That's just

517
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:33,113
a literary device I used because I wanted

518
00:34:33,864 --> 00:34:35,699
to emphasize the word "absolute."

519
00:34:38,243 --> 00:34:40,329
Both your spelling
and your formula are a mess.

520
00:34:41,830 --> 00:34:43,165
Does it even have an answer?

521
00:34:43,248 --> 00:34:44,208
Of course.

522
00:34:44,291 --> 00:34:46,043
I've been working
on this problem alone lately.

523
00:34:46,752 --> 00:34:47,586
So what's the solution?

524
00:34:49,838 --> 00:34:50,798
There is

525
00:34:52,174 --> 00:34:53,509
only one possible answer.

526
00:34:57,930 --> 00:34:59,014
To me…

527
00:35:04,978 --> 00:35:05,979
To me,

528
00:35:06,980 --> 00:35:07,981
